Movie: The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo

Review: Fincher sardonically laying down the blueprint for action thrillers in this dreadful new era where nothing ever matters and streaming executives give notes that content isn’t “second screen enough”: 1) a sick opening credits sequence (that playfully promises exactly the film we’re not about to get) 2) globetrotting location shooting (that intentionally shows only the boring parts of those cities) 3) a perfectly choreographed fight scene (but only one for the entire runtime and nothing more)check those three boxes…
